From: Hangyu Hua <hbh25y@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Jun 2022 14:34:18 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] net: tipc: fix possible refcount leak in tipc_sk_create()
Git-commit: 00aff3590fc0a73bddd3b743863c14e76fd35c0c
Patch-mainline: v5.19-rc5
References: CVE-2022-49620 bsc#1239002

Free sk in case tipc_sk_insert() fails.

Signed-off-by: Hangyu Hua <hbh25y@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Tung Nguyen <tung.q.nguyen@dektech.com.au>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 net/tipc/socket.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/net/tipc/socket.c
+++ b/net/tipc/socket.c
@@ -442,6 +442,7 @@ static int tipc_sk_create(struct net *ne
 	sock_init_data(sock, sk);
 	tipc_set_sk_state(sk, TIPC_OPEN);
 	if (tipc_sk_insert(tsk)) {
+		sk_free(sk);
 		pr_warn("Socket create failed; port number exhausted\n");
 		return -EINVAL;
 	}
